eir start and end times, and use <strong>Month<\/strong> view to get a calendar overview of each month.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>In addition, use the <strong>+Export Events <\/strong>button to download the calendar as a .ics file that can be imported into your own calendar applications (e.g. Outlook).<\/p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"\/>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>ALLIANCE WAR &#8211; <em>Beowulf, Hero of the Geats<\/em><\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"576\" src=\"http:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/LB_Beowulf-1024x576.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-962\" srcset=\"https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/LB_Beowulf-1024x576.png 1024w, https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/LB_Beowulf-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/LB_Beowulf-768x432.png 768w, https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/LB_Beowulf-1536x864.png 1536w, https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/LB_Beowulf.png 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><strong>STARTS:<\/strong> 14th January, 15:00 UTC<br><strong>ENDS:<\/strong> 18th January, 09:00 UTC<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>Before the Cataclysm and the shattering of Kingdoms, Beowulf\u2019s courage and prowess protected the innocent from beasts and tyrants. His conviction and determination helped his people thrive, granting peace and prosperity for all.During a summer night a ferocious storm lashed itself against the Castle. The flashes of lightning lit Beowulf&#8217;s throne room as shadows flickered and danced around him. As his gaze fell upon his golden throne a bloodied figure dressed in black sat upon it. Beowulf&#8217;s hand grabbed the hilt of his legendary Sword, Hrunting.<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>\u201cShow your face Demon, or face the consequences.\u201d<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>The shadowy figure stood from the throne and began her descent, leaving behind blood stained footprints.<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>\u201cI am no Demon, my name is Baba Yaga&#8230; I have been sent here to deliver a message of impending doom. A hero of your strength will be able to halt the devastation.\u201d<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>Beowulf loosened his grip on Hrunting. A warrior&#8217;s taste for battle does not subside with peace.<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>\u201cShow me this vision witch and I will show this evil my power\u201d&nbsp;<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>Baba Yaga lifted her hands and placed them either side of Beowulf\u2019s head. She began muttering a spell as the storm outside intensified. Beowulf was slipping in and out of consciousness before collapsing to the floor.<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>Beowulf was awoken in the throne room by Korthan, his apprentice. Beowulf looked bewildered, his face covered in excitement and fear.<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>\u201cI have been granted a vision. A ferocious evil will invade our land. A monster with purple skin, burning red eyes and armor covered in the skulls of the fallen.\u201d<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>He left in haste, battling through mountains and valleys infested with deadly creatures to reach the Nexus caverns. As he entered the darkness surrounded him. He heard a faint whisper in the shadows, the sound of Baba Yaga leading him down the darkened corridors. Beowulf trawled through the caverns for days until a flickering of light appeared in the distance. He approached with caution with his unsheathed sword. The cavern opened into a cave, revealing the Nexus.<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>Beowulf approached the Nexus.<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>\u201cThe witch granted me a vision of destruction and flame. Where can I find this creature!\u201d<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>The thoughts of the Nexus penetrated Beowulf&#8217;s mind.<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>\u201cThe witch has told no lie, a great evil is coming. Let me grant you my strength and I shall guide you to this evil.\u201d<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>Beowulf did not hesitate, he laid his hand upon the Nexus. Energy began surging into his body, causing him to howl in pain.<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>\u201cWHAT ARE YOU DOING TO ME!\u201d<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>His skin began to turn a purple hue, his eyes filled with blood and his mind began to lose control. The Nexus spoke to him for his final moments.<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>\u201cHow can you destroy a monster when you become one? You will now follow my commands and begin the destruction of your world. You shall be feared by all under a new name, one that will haunt those fortunate to survive\u2026.&nbsp; Almarand\u201d.<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>BEOWULF<\/strong>, legendary Hero of the Geats, arrives in the Shattered Kingdoms, eager to exact revenge on Almarand with his powerful Corrupted Spearmen and Archers:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"608\" height=\"554\" src=\"https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Beowulf-Skills4.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-975\" srcset=\"https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Beowulf-Skills4.png 608w, https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.